 How Does a Computer Think Differently From a Human Brain?
A computer does not understand reality the way we do.
It understands logic, symbols and patterns. Humans process
meaning, consciousness, emotions and memory.

At the deepest level computers only understand: 1 = ON, 0 = OFF.
Binary is the alphabet of machines.

AI is good at predicting patterns inside massive amounts of data.
Computer memory is exact, organized and stable.
Human memory is emotional, biased and unstable.

Current AI is advanced statistical prediction — not human
like consciousness. Consciousness in AI is undiscovered.

## What Is an Algorithm Really?
A baby cannot do anything unless it is taught patterns —
language, faces, responses. A computer is exactly the same.

Is intelligence simply a very complex collection of algorithms?

Imagine two entities:
One feels emotions, makes mistakes, understands meaning.
Second solves every problem perfectly, has no emotions,
has no self awareness.

The first one would be intelligent from my point of view.
A machine with no self awareness will never know when it 
is wrong.

Consciousness in AI is undiscovered, yet the race to making
machines capable of emotions is increasing day by day.
Once combined, Neuroscience will be formed.
